snippet.textDisplay: I think you're misunderstanding this build somewhat. The adult form doesn't need to be a powerhouse because it's literally only intended for breeding and lives only for a few weeks. Compare that to the multiple years of playtime as a larva, and you can easily see why it'd be a waste to allocate any stats over the minimum. Like you say, the adult is just a vessel to complete the main quest, while the larva is very minmaxed for the environment, so why should the adult form be buffed? Trying to maximize literally all aspects of your build is a noob mistake. Winners focus on the strengths and make the weaknesses inconsequential instead.
snippet.textOriginal: I think you're misunderstanding this build somewhat. The adult form doesn't need to be a powerhouse because it's literally only intended for breeding and lives only for a few weeks. Compare that to the multiple years of playtime as a larva, and you can easily see why it'd be a waste to allocate any stats over the minimum. Like you say, the adult is just a vessel to complete the main quest, while the larva is very minmaxed for the environment, so why should the adult form be buffed?
